AB  - In modern port operations, collaborative optimization of berth allocation and tugboat scheduling is a key challenge to improving operational efficiency. To address this problem, this paper proposes an improved quantum lion swarm optimization algorithm(QLSO) to optimize port berth-tugboat cooperative scheduling. The algorithm enhances population diversity by introducing a quantum bit perturbation mechanism, adopts a quantum revolving door search strategy to improve the local search ability, and combines a dynamic role allocation mechanism to balance the exploration and exploitation performance of the algorithm. The experimental results show that, compared to the traditional particle swarm algorithm(PSO) and the genetic algorithm(GA), QLSO exhibits faster convergence speed and better solution quality in both standard test functions and real scheduling scenarios, and is especially suitable for the optimization of large-scale complex scheduling problems. This study not only provides a new efficient optimization tool for intelligent port scheduling, but also provides a new solution idea for the cooperative optimization problem of complex logistics systems.
ER  - 

