AB  - This study highlights the contributions of digital transformation to operational processes and sectoral development in port operations. Digitalization has been found to yield significant outcomes in terms of accelerating processes, strengthening occupational safety, improving operational efficiency, and enhancing coordination among stakeholders. The case analysis conducted at Borusan Port, supported by field data and literature, demonstrates that digitalization not only improves operational efficiency but also provides strategic advantages. In conclusion, digital transformation offers ports not only operational benefits but also competitive advantages. This study contributes to the engineering management and logistics literature and serves as a reference for future smart port applications.
